<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm">
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Closed_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Closed_curve">
A <b>Closed_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> that is traced by a moving point 
that returns to an arbitrary starting <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Closed_curve.wr:IP1">
A <b>Closed_curve</b> shall not be self intersecting.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Composite_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve">

A <b>Composite_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> that combines more than one 
 <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> into its structure.  The <b>Composite_curve</b> shall be continuous.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve.curve_segment">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> for the <b>Composite_curve</b>.
There shall be one or more  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> for a <b>Composite_curve</b>.
No  <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment"/> shall be specified more than once as a <b>curve_segment</b> for a particular <b>Composite_curve</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Composite_curve_segment +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment">
	A <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> is a segment of a 
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/>. 
	A <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> associates 
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve">Curves</express_ref> 
	with a  
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> 
	to help compose the  
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- using_curves -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment.using_curves">
	specifies an inverse relationship that specifies that the existence of the <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> is dependent on the existence of the  
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> 
	that specifies the <b>Composite_curve_segment</b> as its 
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve.curve_segment"/>. 
	There shall be one or more  
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve">Composite_curve</express_ref> 
	for a <b>Composite_curve_segment</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- segment_curve -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve_segment.segment_curve">
	specifies the role of the 
	<express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> 
	for the <b>Composite_curve_segment</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Trimmed_curve +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve">
<p>
A <b>Trimmed_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> 
that has a defined, finite extent.  
</p>
<note>
The <b>Trimmed_curve</b> is necessary to support the specification of 
precise, metric geometry.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve.end_point">
<p>
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Trimmed_curve</b>.  
The <b>end_point</b> is the terminating <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>.
</p></ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve.start_point">
<p>
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Trimmed_curve</b>.  
The <b>start_point</b> is the initiating <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/>.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_curve_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  
   <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path"> 
A <b>Measurement_path</b>  is  a path, direction, or domain of applicability for a dimension or tolerance. The path is represented by a   <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/>. A <b>Measurement_path</b>  is a general term whose meaning depends on the context entity which is using it.  
<example>A surface may only need to be smooth in one direction.</example>
<example>A dimension of a fillet may be specified by its arc length, which is a measurement path.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_by 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path.defined_by">
	specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> for the <b>Measurement_path</b>.  
	The <b>defined_by</b> is the <express_ref linkend="Basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> along which the measurement takes place, or a requirement applies.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_in 
 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_curve_arm.Measurement_path.defined_in">
	specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/> for the <b>Measurement_path</b>.  
	The <b>defined_in</b> is the <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Geometric_coordinate_space"/> that identifies the geometric context in which the measurement path is evaluated.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>

